NAME

   mnttsk_rda_alarms - Initialization Task For RDA Alarms Data Store

SYNOPSIS

   mnttsk_rda_alarms [-t action] [-h]

DESCRIPTION

This process performs initialization of the RDA Alarms linear buffer.  The
RDA Alarms linear buffer (ORPGDAT_RDA_ALARMS) contains an entry for each RDA
alarm code which has been found in RDA status messages sent from the RDA.  The
maximum number of alarm messages which can be saved is configurable.  When the
maximum number is reached, new alarm messages overwrite the oldest messages. 

The startup action can take on one of the following values:  "startup",
"restart", and "clear".  For each action, the following steps are performed: 

   startup:
   restart:

      Currently, there are no defined initializations actions for "startup"
      and "restart".

   clear:

      All LB messages within LB ID ORPGDAT_RDA_ALARMS are removed.

   Options
	-t mode		startup mode.  Determines which initialization actions
			to be performed.  Supported startup modes are "startup"
			and "restart".  By default, the mode is "restart".  

	-h		Provides command line help.


